stabilize Visual Studio and make the best use of your i9 processor and 64GB DDR5 RAM, here are some settings and optimizations:

1. Optimize Visual Studio Settings
Disable CodeLens: It can be resource-intensive. Go to Options > Text Editor > All Languages > CodeLens and uncheck "Enable CodeLens."
Adjust Project Load Settings: Disable or limit auto-load for extensions in Extensions > Manage Extensions to reduce startup load.
